TITLE: Health - Garden for the disabled at Heidelberg Day Care Centre, Melbourne - An innovative walled and partly elevated garden has been constructed on what was formerly waste ground - The garden area is a complex of walled garden beds at different levels with sloping walkways and steps and rails - This enables aged persons in wheelchairs to navigate the area and tend their garden from the wheelchair - While the steps and rails provide an excellent exercising area for other patients with walking disabilities - The layout has proved a great success from both moral and therapeutic angles CATEGORY: photograph FORMAT: colour negative STATUS: Preservation Material

TITLE: Research - Health and food - Medical research in Melbourne - Research at Monash University, Melbourne aimed at attempting to establish the genetic basis for the rapid emergence and spread of multiple antibiotic resistance causing concern at hospitals - Dr Ron Skurray, Senior Lecturer in Microbiology is shown here loading DNA samples isolated from antibiotic resistant strains of bacteria on to an Agarose slab gel prior to electrophoresis. TITLE: Construction of Snowy Mountains Hydro Electric Scheme - panorama, Tumut 1 machine hall rock bolts - Panorama showing overbreak in Machine Hall, downstream side near reference lines (5) and (6) where rock fall occurred on 26th March, 1956. Joint plane controlling top of fall clearly visible, also joints at back of rock fall. White rings around drill holes indicate from where roof bolts pulled out on 28th March, 1956. Roof bolts in top left hand side with loose bearing plates previously support a slab of rock which was later detached by deliberately blasting from behind these supporting bolts. The black hose protruding from the roof was installed in diamond drill hole No. 5461 by the contractor, to divert water away from the face while working. CATEGORY: photograph FORMAT: b&w negative STATUS: Preservation material
